apper class that sits on top of `IFileSystem` and provides a cleaner, simpler API for common file operations rather than exposing everything. I could build something that wraps the real `FileSystem` and handles the most frequently used methods in a more convenient way. I'm torn between generating a reasonable wrapper pattern and asking for clarification, since \"file system wrapper\" could mean different things. Let me just ask the user what they're actually trying to accomplish rather than guessing.","outputTokens":987,"requestId":"982B:1B0168:11B35C9:1625598:69FFE659"},"id":"186042fd-4fdf-4644-90e8-db60125aa8ab","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:59:11.284Z","parentId":"2d6ec344-2116-4d0f-839d-4b9ffec7bc80"}
